<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC) No 3117/85 of 4 November 1985 laying down general rules on the granting of compensatory indemnities in respect of sardines </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 3117/85, millega n&auml;hakse ette sardiinide eest makstava tasandush&uuml;vitiste &uuml;ldeeskirjad 4. november 1985 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty of Accession of Spain and Portugal and in particular Article 2 (3) and the Act annexed to that Treaty, and in particular Articles 171 and 358 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Hispaania ja Portugali &uuml;hinemislepingut, eelk&otilde;ige selle artikli 2 l&otilde;iget 3, ning nimetatud lepingule lisatud akti, eelk&otilde;ige selle artikleid 171 ja 358, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Act of Accession of Spain and Portugal provides for a special system for the move towards alignment of sardine prices, in the new Member States and in the Member States of the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986, on the level of Mediterranean prices; whereas this system is accompanied by the establishment, as from the date of accession, of a compensatory indemnity system for sardine producers in the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986, for which detailed implementing rules require to be drawn up by 31 December 1985 at the latest; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Hispaania ja Portugali &uuml;hinemisakt n&auml;eb uutes liikmesriikides ja 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduses ette eris&uuml;steemi sardiinihindade l&auml;hendamiseks Vahemere hindadele; selle s&uuml;steemiga kaasneb sardiinitootjatele 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduses alates &uuml;hinemise kuup&auml;evast tasandush&uuml;vitiste s&uuml;steemi kehtestamine, mille &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad on vaja koostada hiljemalt 31. detsembriks 1985; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this special system for the move towards price alignment has a direct influence on the level of income of producers of Atlantic sardines in the Member States of the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986 and whereas it alters the existing balance in sardine production in the said Community; </inglise>
<eesti> hindade l&auml;hendamise eris&uuml;steemil on vahetu m&otilde;ju atlandi sardiini tootjate sissetulekutele 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduse liikmesriikides ning see muudab sardiinitootmise senist tasakaalu k&otilde;nealuses &uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this new situation, by altering the conditions of competition in the markets of the Member States of the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986, also influences the level of income of sardine producers of those Member States in the Mediterranean region; </inglise>
<eesti> muutes konkurentsitingimusi 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduse liikmesriikide turgudel, m&otilde;jutab see uus olukord vahetult sardiinitootjate sissetuleku taset neis k&otilde;nealustest liikmesriikidest, mis asuvad Vahemere &auml;&auml;res; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, consequently, general rules on the granting of these indemnities should be established; whereas the detailed rules laid down for the move towards price alignment are such that a differentiation in the terms on which the indemnities are granted should be made between Atlantic and Mediterranean producers; </inglise>
<eesti> sellest tulenevalt tuleks kehtestada nende h&uuml;vitiste maksmise &uuml;ldeeskirjad; hindade l&auml;hendamiseks etten&auml;htud &uuml;ksikasjalike eeskirjade alusel tuleb Atlandi ja Vahemere tootjatele ette n&auml;ha erinevad tingimused, mille alusel h&uuml;vitisi maksta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the indemnity granted for Mediterranean sardines is phased over the period of the move towards price alignment; whereas the rate of phased reduction results from the price level fixed annually by the Council; </inglise>
<eesti> vahemere sardiinide eest makstavat h&uuml;vitist v&auml;hendatakse hindade l&auml;hendamise aja jooksul astmeliselt; astmelise v&auml;hendamise m&auml;&auml;r tuleneb igal aastal n&otilde;ukogu poolt kinnitatavast hinnatasemest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the terms on which indemnity is granted for Mediterranean sardines must take into account, on the one hand, the effects of alterations in the conditions of competition on the income of the producers concerned and, on the other hand, the necessity of compensating for the price difference between the dominant productions of the Mediterranean and the Atlantic without introducing elements distorting the conditions of competition between processors in the enlarged Community, </inglise>
<eesti> tingimused, mille alusel makstakse h&uuml;vitist vahemere sardiinide eest, peavad arvesse v&otilde;tma &uuml;hest k&uuml;ljest konkurentsitingimuste muutuse m&otilde;ju asjaomaste tootjate sissetulekutele ja teisest k&uuml;ljest vajadust h&uuml;vitada Vahemere ja Atlandi olulisemate toodete hinnaerinevused valitseva tootmise vahel, moonutamata seejuures konkurentsitingimusi laienenud &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;tlejate vahel, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation lays down general rules on the granting of compensatory indemnities to sardine producers in the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986 during the period of the move towards sardine price alignment as defined by the Act of Accession of Spain and Portugal. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus s&auml;testab &uuml;ldeeskirjad tasandush&uuml;vitiste maksmiseks 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduse sardiinitootjatele sardiinihindade l&auml;hendamise aja jooksul, nagu see on m&auml;&auml;ratletud Hispaania ja Portugali &uuml;hinemisaktis. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A compensatory indemnity shall be granted for Atlantic sardines produced in the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986: </inglise>
<eesti> Tasandush&uuml;vitist antakse 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduses toodetud atlandi sardiinide eest: </eesti>
<inglise> - which are of qualities E and A, as defined by Regulation (EEC) No 103/76 (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3166/82 (2), </inglise>
<eesti> - mis kuuluvad kvaliteediklassi E ja A vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 103/76 (1) m&auml;&auml;ratlusele, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 3166/82, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> - which are offered for sale for human consumption within a limit of 2 000 tonnes per year, by producers' organizations within the meaning of Article 5 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 3796/81 (3), at prices at least equal to the Community withdrawal price as defined in Article 12 (1) of the last mentioned Regulation, but lower than a guaranteed minimum price, and </inglise>
<eesti> - mida tootjaorganisatsioonid m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3796/81 (3) artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses pakuvad m&uuml;&uuml;giks toiduna kuni 2000 tonni aastas hinnaga, mis on v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;rdne &uuml;henduse k&otilde;rvaldamishinnaga viimati nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 12 l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses, ent alla tagatud miinimumhinna, ning </eesti>
<inglise> - which are intended for processing. </inglise>
<eesti> - mis on m&otilde;eldud t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The indemnity shall be granted to producers' organizations provided that </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitist antakse tootjaorganisatsioonidele tingimusel, et: </eesti>
<inglise> - they were established and recognized under Regulation (EEC) No 3796/81 before Accession, and </inglise>
<eesti> - nad on asutatud ja tunnustatud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3796/81 alusel enne &uuml;hinemist ning </eesti>
<inglise> - during the two years preceding the date of Accession they applied sardine withdrawal prices, the conditions laid down in Article 13 of Regulation (EEC) No 3796/81 being observed. </inglise>
<eesti> - nad on kahe aasta jooksul enne &uuml;hinemiskuup&auml;eva kohaldanud sardiini k&otilde;rvaldamishinda, j&auml;rgides m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3796/81 artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud tingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The guaranteed minimum price specified in paragraph 1 shall be the withdrawal price applied during the last year preceding Accession corrected in line with any charge applicable to the guide price for the coming fishing year. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud tagatud miinimumhinnaks on viimase &uuml;hinemiseelse aasta jooksul kohaldatud k&otilde;rvaldamishind, mida on korrigeeritud vastavalt tuleval kalandusaastal kohaldatava soovitushinna suhtes kehtivale maksule. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The indemnity shall be equal to the difference between the selling price received by the producer and the guaranteed minimum price. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitis v&otilde;rdub tootja saadava m&uuml;&uuml;gihinna ja tagatud miinimumhinna vahega. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The financial compensation provided for in Article 13 of Regulation (EEC) No 3796/81 shall be calculated on the basis of the guaranteed minimum price as defined in paragraph 3. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3796/81 artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud rahaline kompensatsioon arvutatakse tagatud miinimumhinna alusel, nagu see on m&auml;&auml;ratletud l&otilde;ikes 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A compensatory indemnity shall be granted in respect of Mediterranean sardines produced within the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986 provided that: </inglise>
<eesti> Tasandush&uuml;vitist antakse 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduses toodetud vahemere sardiinide eest: </eesti>
<inglise> - they are of sizes 3 or 4 and of qualities E and A as defined in Regulation (EEC) No 103/76, </inglise>
<eesti> - mis kuuluvad suurusr&uuml;hma 3 v&otilde;i 4 ja kvaliteediklassi E ja A vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 103/76 (1) m&auml;&auml;ratlusele, </eesti>
<inglise> - they are sold and actually delivered within a limit of 43 000 tonnes per annum for processing into preserved fish falling within heading No 16.04 of the Common Customs Tariff or into salted products put up in hermetically sealed containers, and </inglise>
<eesti> - mida m&uuml;&uuml;akse ja tarnitakse tegelikult kuni 43 000 tonni aastas, et t&ouml;&ouml;delda neid &uuml;hise tollitariifistiku rubriiki nr 16.04 kuuluvateks kalakonservideks v&otilde;i hermeetiliselt suletud pakendites soolatud toodeteks, ning </eesti>
<inglise> - their selling price at the first marketing stage is at least the Community withdrawal price. </inglise>
<eesti> - mille m&uuml;&uuml;gihind esimeses turustusetapis v&otilde;rdub v&auml;hemalt &uuml;henduse k&otilde;rvaldamishinnaga. </eesti>
<inglise> That price shall be increased, for each of the categories of the products in question, by at least the difference between the withdrawal price for Atlantic and Mediterranean sardines applicable in the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda hinda suurendatakse iga k&otilde;nealuse tootekategooria puhul v&auml;hemalt 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduses kohaldatavate atlandi ja vahemere sardiini k&otilde;rvaldamishindade vahe v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The quantities qualifying for the indemnity shall be determined for each producers' organization or for each producer on the basis of the quantities delivered for processing as specified in paragraph 1 during the period 1982 to 1984. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitise saamise tingimustele vastavad kogused m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks iga tootjaorganisatsiooni v&otilde;i tootja puhul koguste p&otilde;hjal, mis on ajavahemikus 1982-1984 vastavalt l&otilde;ikele 1 t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks toodud. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The indemnity shall be equal to the difference between the withdrawal price for Atlantic sardines of the size in question applicable in the Community as constituted before 1 January 1986 and the withdrawal price of Atlantic sardines of size 2 applicable in the new Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitis v&otilde;rdub 1986. aasta 1. jaanuari eelse koosseisuga &uuml;henduses k&otilde;nealuse suurusega atlandi sardiini suhtes kohaldatava k&otilde;rvaldamishinna ja uutes liikmesriikides 2. suurusr&uuml;hma atlandi sardiini suhtes kohaldatava k&otilde;rvaldamishinna vahega. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The indemnity shall be paid to processors. </inglise>
<eesti> H&uuml;vitist makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tlejatele. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The premium provided for in Article 14 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 3796/81 may not be aggregated with the allowance provided for in this Article. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3796/81 artikli 14 l&otilde;ikes 3 osutatud lisatasu ei v&otilde;i k&auml;esolevas artiklis s&auml;testatud toetusele lisada. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Detailed rules for the application of this Regulation shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 33 of Regulation (EEC) No 3796/81. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad v&otilde;etakse vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3796/81 artiklis 33 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 1 January 1986 subject to the entry into force of the Treaty of Accession of Spain and Portugal. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 1. jaanuaril 1986 vastavalt Hispaania ja Portugali &uuml;hinemislepingu j&otilde;ustumisele. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from 1 March 1986. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda kohaldatakse alates 1. m&auml;rtsist 1986. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 4 November 1985. </inglise>
